      "paragraph_name": "FUNC-CODES",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This data structure defines a set of constants that represent different IMS (Information Management System) function codes. These codes are used when making calls to the IMS database to specify the type of operation to be performed. The function codes include 'GU' (Get Unique), 'GHU' (Get Hold Unique), 'GN' (Get Next), 'GHN' (Get Hold Next), 'GNP' (Get Next within Parent), 'GHNP' (Get Hold Next within Parent), 'REPL' (Replace), 'ISRT' (Insert), and 'DLET' (Delete). Each function code is a 4-character alphanumeric field with a predefined value. These values are used in the program logic to determine the specific IMS operation to be executed. The structure itself does not perform any processing but provides a central location for defining and accessing these IMS function codes.",
